Let's think about how to bound the difference. For any i, if the i-th term in the sum for m is f(x_i) and the i-th term in the sum for n is f(y_i), then |f(x_i) - f(y_i)| < ε₁ if |x_i - y_i| < δ.

The difference between the sums will be the sum of terms of the form (f(x_i) - f(y_i)) * Δx. The total difference will be bounded by the sum of |f(x_i) - f(y_i)| * |Δx|.

