/- The definition of uniform continuity on a set S: for every ε > 0, there exists a δ > 0 such that for all x, y ∈ S, if |y - x| < δ, then |f y - f x| < ε. -/
def UnifContOn (f : ℝ → ℝ) (S : Set ℝ) : Prop :=
  ∀ ε > 0, ∃ δ > 0, ∀ x ∈ S, ∀ y ∈ S, |y - x| < δ → |f y - f x| < ε

